<statement type='proposition'>
  ‖ The additive identity for $𝗭$ is $\eqc{(0, 0)}$. ⦉
</statement>
<statement type='proposition'>
  ‖ The multiplicative identity for $𝗭$ is $\eqc{(1, 0)}$. ⦉
</statement>

§ Notation ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ We denote the additive identity of $𝗭$ by $0_{𝗭}$ and the
    multiplicative identity by $1_{𝗭}$. ⦉

  ‖ When it is clear from context, we call $0_{𝗭}$ “zero” and
    we call $1_{𝗭}$ “one”. ⦉
⦉

